commText: Gaikwad and Ravindra are at the crease. Gaikwad is on strike. Khaleel Ahmed will open the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Gaikwad, 1 run, length ball slanting across onto off stump. Punched towards cover point and the batters scamper through to allow the CSK skipper off the mark
Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, no run, good length and a bit of shape away from the batter. Guided off the outside half towards that fourth slip fielder
Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, no run, back of length and offers width. Ravindra throws his bat at it but it wobbles away past his bat
Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, no run, back of length and slanting inwards this time towards off stump. Punched to covers
Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, 1 run, fuller delivery onto off stump, Ravindra with a push towards mid-off for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Gaikwad, wide, full but angling across, a bit too wide outside off and Ruturaj shoulders arms
Khaleel Ahmed to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Gaikwad, out Caught by Pant!! Superb inswinger from Khaleel, too good for Ruturaj. Jumps up and punches the air the delight. A length ball that pitches on off and moves devilishly inwards after pitching to get a faint inside edge onto the keeper. Delhi get the early wicket they would have desired, superb first over from Khaleel! Gaikwad c Pant b Khaleel Ahmed 1(2)
Ajinkya Rahane, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Ishant Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Ishant to Ravindra, no run, on a length and wide outside off. Rachin slashes at it but can't connect
Ishant to Ravindra, no run, 137.8 clicks, hits the deck hard on a length outside off and gets some away movement. Another swing and miss for Rachin
Ruturaj vs LA pace this IPL Innings: 3 Balls: 16 Runs: 17 Dismissals: 3
Ishant to Ravindra, no run, back of length delivery in that corridor of uncertainity. Ravindra tried to punch it away but beaten on the outside edge
Ishant to Ravindra, 1 run, seemed like a knuckle ball, goes full outside off. Ravindra slices it behind square. Couple of bounces towards wide third-man
Ishant to Rahane, no run, good length outside off, Rahane cuts it but cuts towards the point fielder
Ishant to Rahane, wide, on a length and angling inwards, slides down the leg side
Ishant to Rahane, 1 run, back of length onto the thigh pad, tucked behind square for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Rahane, leg byes, 1 run, jags back in from a length and onto the pads. Edged behind square for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, no run, 137.7 clicks, full and shaping away quite a bit. Rachin with a loose drive away from the body. Once again only connects with air

Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, no run, short of length and shaping away outside off. Rachin still not able to adjust for the swing, he's clutching at nothing out here!! Seems to be struggling a bit against Khaleel
Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, no run, short and wide, shapes away again. Rachin tries a big swipe across the line but no connection with the ball once again
Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! This wicket was always on the cards!! Khaleel was totally bossing this exchange and rightly gets the wicket. A short of length delivery, shapes away from off as Rachin tries a big swipe across the line. Top-edges it over the bowler's head and Stubbs from mid-off runs to his left to take a well judged catch. Both CSK openers out cheaply, that's been a rarity. Khaleel is in the middle of a dream spell out here... Ravindra c Tristan Stubbs b Khaleel Ahmed 2(12)
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Khaleel Ahmed to Mitchell, no run, 140.4 clicks, full delivery onto off, shapes away and beats the outside edge as Mitchell was defending for the ball that comes back in.
Ishant to Rahane, no run, good length onto off stump, punched towards covers
Ishant to Rahane, no run, good length and wide outside off, cut towards the point fielder
Ishant to Rahane, 1 run, slower delivery, floated onto off stump. Driven down the ground for a single
Ishant to Mitchell, 1 run, good length and outside off, punched square of the wicket for a single

Ishant to Rahane, FOUR, first shot off the middle of the bat and the first boundary!! A back of length delivery, angling inwards towards off stump. Not quite short enough and Rahane hoists his pull over the infield. One bounce and over

Ishant to Rahane, FOUR, four more!! On a length and outside off, Rahane waits and plays it late to get it past the point fielder on the punch. Gets a bit of Test match guile into this T20 game to score his second boundary
Khaleel Ahmed to Mitchell, 1 run, fuller and shaping away from off. Mitchell shuffles inwards and pushes it softly towards point for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Rahane, 1 run, fuller delivery, angling across naturally. Driven to the left of the cover fielder for a single
The ball has stopped swinging now. Playing Khaleel will be a bit easier..

Khaleel Ahmed to Mitchell, FOUR, fuller and angling across onto fourth stump, draws Mitchell forward on the drive and gets the edge. Runs away between first and fourth slip for a boundary. Khaleel has his hands on his head
Khaleel Ahmed to Mitchell, no run, shortens the length slightly and as a result gets a bit more away shape on this one. Beats the outside edge
Khaleel Ahmed to Mitchell, no run, full onto off stump. Driven towards mid-off

Khaleel Ahmed to Mitchell, no run, good length delivery onto off stump. Punched into the ground towards the point fielder. For the second game in a row, Khaleel Ahmed ends up conceding only 9 runs after bowling three in the powerplay.

Summary (Overs 1-5) -- Brilliant start from Khaleel and DC -- Ruturaj caught-behind for 1 (0.6) -- Rachin dismissed for 2 off 12 balls (2.5) -- Both wickets taken by Khaleel -- Takes 23 balls for first boundary of CSK innings
Anrich Nortje, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Nortje to Rahane, no run, 142 clicks, shapes in after pitching and Rahane tried to flick it away. Only manages an inside edge onto his pads
Nortje to Rahane, SIX, I0$ Full and slants onto the pads, effortlessly flicked over the deep backward square leg fielder for a six!!
Nortje to Rahane, 1 run, good length and a bit wide, punched behind square for a single
Nortje to Mitchell, 1 run, 144.8 clicks, inswinger from a length towards the top of off. Inside edge onto the back pad and the batters steal a quick run
Nortje to Rahane, no run, full on off stump, Rahane closes the bat face on the drive but towards mid-wicket it goes

Nortje to Rahane, leg byes, 1 run, length ball that jags in after pitching and Rahane plays the wrong line trying to flick. Off his thigh pad towards silly point and once again a quick leg bye taken. End of a very productive powerplay for DC. Not many teams are going to be able to have CSK in this type of position after six, they can be proud of themselves
Rasikh Dar comes on as impact sub, replacing Prithvi Shaw
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Rahane vs Axar Patel in IPL (before today): Runs: 80 Balls: 61 One Dismissal Avg: 80.0 SR: 131.15
Axar to Rahane, 1 run, short on middle and leg, Rahane pulls to the left of deep backward square. Fielder gets across quickly to cut it off
Axar to Mitchell, 1 run, 94.3kph length ball sliding in on middle, Mitchell punches off the back foot to long-on
Axar to Rahane, no run, 93.8kph, length ball just outside off, Rahane gets forward and punches to short cover
Axar to Rahane, 1 run, 93.9kph, tossed up just outside off, Rahane gets forward and knocks it wide of short cover

Axar to Mitchell, 2 runs, much flatter and quicker to Mitchell. 100kph, darted in on a length outside off, Mitchell stays back and taps it wide of point. There's a shy at the non-striker's end, and it gives away an overthrow
Axar to Mitchell, 1 run, punched off the back foot to long-on
Rasikh Dar into the attack. Bowls right-arm medium pace
Rasikh Dar Salam, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, 1 run, 132kph, short of length on off, Mitchell looks to punch hard down the ground and it goes off a thick edge to deep third

Rasikh Salam to Rahane, FOUR, 132.4kph length ball straying on middle and leg, and Rahane capitalises! He hangs back and whips it behind square, getting it nice and fine. Fielder in the deep is quite square
Rasikh Salam to Rahane, 1 run, 135kph short of length delivery just outside off, Rahane chops it into the pitch as he's cramped for room on the cut
Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, 2 runs, slower length ball on off, Mitchell clips it gently in front of square, realises it's in the gap and comes back for two

Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, no run, this one has gone right through him! Length ball around off, Mitchell is rooted to the crease as he looks to punch down the ground but the ball nips in sharply. It goes through bat and pad, and bounces over the top of the stumps

Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, leg byes, 1 run, big appeal from Rasikh but gets no support! Slower off-cutter that dips and turns as Mitchell looks to go for a slog. He's struck on the pad. Would've missed leg stump as it turned quite a bit
Rahane batting well, but Mitchell struggling for rhythm. Asking rate has crept over 12
Axar to Mitchell, 1 run, flat on off, back of a length, Mitchell hangs back and looks to loft down the ground. He miscues it off the splice over the umpire's head
Axar to Rahane, 1 run, flat on middle and leg, length ball, Rahane bends low and pulls to deep backward square
Axar to Mitchell, SIX, that's his strength! Excellent use of the feet, gets close enough and then launches it straight down the ground. Such a lovely player to watch when hitting straight
Axar to Mitchell, no run, looks to push straight but gets a thick edge to short third
Axar to Mitchell, 2 runs, dances down looking to hit down the ground again, but isn't quite to the pitch this time. Ends up dragging it off a thick inside edge behind square
Axar to Mitchell, 1 run, length ball sliding in on off, Mitchell is cramped for room as he punches wide of cover

Timeout! CSK need a move-on now. This partnership has done a good rebuilding job after those two early wickets, but the asking rate has gone over 12. Also, while these two are at the crease, it's a good opportunity for DC to slip through the overs of Axar as Dube is still waiting in the hut.

Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, 2 runs, immediately after the timeout, Mitchell looks to unleash! Length ball on off, he looks to swing it down the ground but drags it off a thick inside edge behind square. Good diving stop in the deep from Nortje
Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, 1 run, slower ball floated up on off, Mitchell hammers it straight but it's cut off at long-off
Rasikh Salam to Rahane, SIX, lovely pick-up shot from Rahane! Gets a half-volley on middle stump at 128kph, and effortlessly whips it over the long leg boundary. The short boundary size also helps

Rasikh Salam to Rahane, 1 run, direct hit at the non-striker's end! Is Rahane safe? Back of a length on off, he taps it wide of cover and sets off for the single. It's tight as the throw hits the stumps, but Rahane is home by a few inches

Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, SIX, another back-of-the-hand slower ball from Rasikh, but this time Mitchell was waiting for it! The ball lands right in the slot, Mitchell clears the front leg and whacks it over long-on. Powerful strike down the ground from the right-hander
Rasikh Salam to Mitchell, 1 run, can't call that a chance, it was hit really hard. Length ball on off, Mitchell smashes it straight and Rasikh does well to get a hand on it, taking pace off

Summary (6-10 overs) – Rahane gets a first six of the innings, flicks Nortje over square leg – Delhi concede just 32 in the powerplay – Mitchell steps out and hits Axar down the ground for six – Rasikh Dar comes on as impact sub, concedes 25 off his first two – CSK on the rebuild, 75/2 after 10
Axar to Mitchell, no run, cuts this to point
Axar to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Axar to Mitchell, out Caught&Bowled!! Simple return catch for Axar! Flat length ball on off, gets big on Mitchell as he looks to loft down the ground and hits him high on the bat resulting in a mishit. It goes to the left of Axar who takes a good low catch. Mitchell c and b Axar 34(26) [4s-1 6s-2]
In walks the impact sub Shivam Dube.
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Axar to Shivam Dube, 1 run, knocks this one down to long-on
Axar to Rahane, 1 run, fired into the pads, Rahane works it down to long-on

Axar to Shivam Dube, no run, was that a chance for Pant? Length ball fired in outside off, Dube goes for a slog-sweep but gets a faint under-edge on it. Pant doesn't get his gloves in the right position and is hit on the pad
Axar to Shivam Dube, 1 run, length ball darted in on leg, Dube tucks it behind square
Mitchell Marsh, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mitchell Marsh to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Dube cuts it to deep point
Mitchell Marsh to Rahane, 2 runs, short of length into the body, slower one, Rahane is late on the pull and mistimes it behind square. He charges back for two as short fine gives chase
Mitchell Marsh vs Shivam Dube in IPL before today Balls: 15 Runs: 9 Outs: 2

Mitchell Marsh to Rahane, FOUR, flies off a thick edge past short third! Short of length outside off, slower one, Rahane slashes hard but it goes off the top-edge and beats everyone. Marsh looks to the heavens in dismay

Mitchell Marsh to Rahane, FOUR, this is really well played! Back of a length on middle and leg, not very short at all, but Rahane picks length early and pulls it through square leg. Timing is sublime!
Mitchell Marsh to Rahane, 1 run, length ball straying down leg, Rahane glances fine but is denied by a diving stop at short fine leg
Mitchell Marsh to Shivam Dube, wide, wide yorker outside off, left alone by Dube and the umpire thinks it's outside the marker and spreads his arms to signal a wide
Mitchell Marsh to Shivam Dube, 1 run, full delivery on middle, Dube knocks it to long-on
Anrich Nortje [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Nortje to Shivam Dube, no run, full outside off, 143kph, Dube swings and misses
This is the matchup DC hope will work in their favour. Nortje to Dube.
Nortje to Shivam Dube, 1 run, 129.3kph length ball on off, Dube looks to slog but gets it high on the bat. It loops over Nortje's head and goes down to long-on
Nortje to Rahane, leg byes, 1 run, another slower one. Length ball on leg stump, probably a leg-cutter, Rahane looks to play across the line but is hit on the thigh pad
Nortje to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, yorker at the toes, Dube does well to squeeze it through the on-side. It's in the gap and he gets back for two

Nortje to Shivam Dube, FOUR, powerfully struck! Full and wide outside off at 143kph, Dube reaches out, goes hard and hammers it over extra cover. Didn't move his feet at all, was all about the hands and upper-body power

Nortje to Shivam Dube, 1 run, complete miscue as he's beaten for pace on the pull shot, but there's no one inside the ring on the on-side! Short of length at the body, rushes onto Dube and he mistimes it in the air. But it lands safely at midwicket
Mukesh is brought into the attack in the 14th over. He's got the role which RR have assigned to Sandeep
Mukesh Kumar, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Shivam Dube, 1 run, length ball on middle and leg, slanted in from round the wicket, Dube hangs back and clips it behind square
Mukesh Kumar to Rahane, no run, back of a length outside off, 135kph, Rahane looks to dab to third but almost chops it back onto his stumps off the under-edge
Mukesh Kumar to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to Rahane, out Caught by Warner!! Rahane looks to slog and perishes! Not really a strength of his. It's the situation that necessitates him to go for it, but he doesn't get hold. It's a slower ball floated up on off, Rahane looks to go over midwicket but slices it off the outside half. Simple catch for Warner at long-on. Rahane c Warner b Mukesh Kumar 45(30) [4s-5 6s-2]

Timeout! DC on top at this stage with the asking rate nearly touching 14. They've used their cutters well, and a tight spell from Axar has also contributed a great deal. He still has one over left, but it's hard to see him bowling now with Dube in the middle.
Sameer Rizvi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Sameer Rizvi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to Sameer Rizvi, out Caught by Khaleel Ahmed!! Well, this is how it goes in this format. Six off his first ball the other day, and now a golden duck. Good length delivery on off, he looks to play across the line, gets a leading edge and it flies to Khaleel at short third. He makes no mistake. Sameer Rizvi c Khaleel Ahmed b Mukesh Kumar 0(1)
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Jadeja, no run, 136.3kph, back of a length on off, Jadeja blocks from the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Jadeja, 1 run, short of length delivery just outside off, Jadeja pulls it to long-on
Ishant Sharma [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack

Ishant to Jadeja, FOUR, Jadeja makes room and hits this hard down the ground to beat mid-off! It wasn't an easy ball to get on top of. It was banged in on a length around middle, and Jadeja had to play on the up. But he did so with elan
Ishant to Jadeja, 1 run, short of length into the body, Jadeja mistimes the pull behind square
Ishant to Shivam Dube, no ball, 1 run, 140.7kph, overpitched outside off, and Dube slices it to deep point. Oh dear, Ishant has overstepped
Ishant to Jadeja, no run, well bowled! Cracking yorker outside off at 145kph, and Jadeja can only squeeze it down the pitch to Ishant. He gathers and has a word or two to say to the batter
Ishant to Jadeja, 1 run, very full outside off, Jadeja can't get under it and drives to long-off
Ishant to Shivam Dube, 1 run, Ishant falls in his followthrough but it's another superb yorker outside off. Dube squeezes it to long-off
Ishant to Jadeja, 1 run, short of length at the body, slower one, Jadeja looks to pull but mistimes it to square leg
Quality over from Ishant, despite that no ball. Required rate has gone close to 16 now.

Summary (10-15 overs) – Axar takes a sharp caught and bowled to dismiss Mitchell – Rahane scores off Marsh but holes out against Mukesh Kumar – Sameer Rizvi out for a first ball duck – Delhi in complete control of the game – CSK need 80 off the final five overs
Nortje from round the wicket
Anrich Nortje [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Nortje to Jadeja, 1 run, full and wide outside off, Jadeja reaches out and slices it on the bounce to sweeper cover
Nortje to Shivam Dube, 1 run, wide yorker at 140kph, Dube squeezes it to extra cover
Not much these two CSK batters can do at the moment with DC bowling really well
Nortje to Jadeja, 1 run, full toss wide of off, Jadeja drives to long-off
Nortje to Shivam Dube, wide, wide yorker attempted, but it's outside the marker and Dube lets it go
Nortje to Shivam Dube, 1 run, full and wide, close to the blockhole, Dube reaches out and slices it on the bounce to deep backward point. DC have got their plans and execution spot on
Nortje to Jadeja, 1 run, wide yorker outside off again, Jadeja squeezes it into the off-side
Nortje to Shivam Dube, 1 run, wide yorker again, and again it's just a single into the off-side. Another top class over
Mukesh Kumar [1.0-0-2-2] is back into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! That's the end of Dube who wasn't allowed to tee off tonight. Excellent execution of plans from DC to bowl it wide outside off. THis is a slower length ball, makes Dube reach out for the big hit and he flat-bats it straight to long-off. Shivam Dube c Tristan Stubbs b Mukesh Kumar 18(17) [4s-1]
Massive ovation for Dhoni who walks out to bat for the first time in this tournament.
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mukesh Kumar to Dhoni, FOUR, it's that easy for him! Stride out to the middle and whack your first ball for four. Crowd goes bonkers. Short of length at the body, Dhoni gets on top of it and nonchalatly pulls it to the long leg boundary
Shivam Dube vs DC in IPL Inns: 8 Runs: 151 Avg: 18.87 SR: 146.6 HS: 32
Mukesh Kumar to Dhoni, 1 run, dropped! Khaleel, who's not done anything wrong so far, puts down a sitter. Full toss outside off, Dhoni slices it straight to backward point but down it goes
Mukesh Kumar to Jadeja, FOUR, unlucky for Mukesh! Goes full and wide, Jadeja barely manages to reach out and get bat on it, but it runs away fine off the toe-end
Mukesh Kumar to Jadeja, 1 run, full and wide outside off, Jadeja slices it to deep backward point
Mukesh Kumar to Dhoni, FOUR, the power of this man! Full and wide outside off, doesn't quite nail the yorker and offers it right in the slot. And Dhoni absolutely clobbers it through extra cover
Khaleel Ahmed [3.0-1-9-2] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Jadeja, 1 run, full toss on off, Jadeja swipes it to deep midwicket, only a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhoni, wide, slower off-cutter outside off, looks to keep it away from Dhoni's hitting arc but it's too wide. Dhoni leaves it alone
MS Dhoni vs Khaleel Ahmed in IPL (before today) Runs: 44 Balls: 23 no dismissal SR: 191.3
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhoni, wide, left alone again and it's another wide outside off
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhoni, 1 run, full and wide, slower one, Dhoni drives gently to long-off
Khaleel Ahmed to Jadeja, no run, low full toss outside off, Jadeja drives to extra cover

Khaleel Ahmed to Jadeja, 1 run, high full toss outside off, and it's slapped hard but straight to deep backward point. Jadeja immediately asks for a no-ball, but the umpire thinks it's below the waist
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhoni, wide, another wide outside off from Khaleel. He's desperately looking to keep it out of Dhoni's zone but has erred thrice in the over already

Khaleel Ahmed to Dhoni, SIX, Dhoni has just rocked up here and smashed 16 off five balls. Slower one floated up outside off, Khaleel looks to keep it wide again but Dhoni reaches out and lofts it beautifully over extra cover for six. What timing from the great man!
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhoni, no run, nails the yorker outside off this time, Dhoni can't do much with it and squeezes it down the pitch
Khaleel bowls out with figures of 2/21! Brilliant spell from the left-armer.
Mukesh Kumar to Jadeja, wide, wide yorker outside off, left alone and the umpire's arms go up
Mukesh Kumar to Jadeja, 1 run, excellent yorker outside off, Jadeja squeezes it into the off-side for a single
Crowd goes "Dhoni, Dhoni"
Mukesh Kumar to Dhoni, no run, another superb wide yorker, Dhoni squeezes it to deep third and turns down the single

Ponting waving his arms from the dugout to get his message across. You got to say outstanding field placement for the wide yorker. Slip, short third man, square third man and backward point. There is no way to smack the wide yorker to the boundary behind square on the off-side
Mukesh Kumar to Dhoni, no run, superb stop from Rasikh to save a certain boundary! Full and wide outside off, Dhoni absolutely hammers it but Rasikh dives to his right at extra cover and cuts it off
Mukesh Kumar to Dhoni, no run, full and wide again, Dhoni looks to go hard and mistmes it to point
Mukesh Kumar to Dhoni, 1 run, very full outside off, Dhoni can't get under it as he drills it to long-off
Mukesh Kumar to Jadeja, 2 runs, full toss outside off, Jadeja shuffles across and looks to slog. He doesn't get hold of it though. Mistimes it through midwicket for a couple of runs
Nortje to close this out. The match is already beyond CSK
Anrich Nortje [3.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack
Nortje to Dhoni, FOUR, it's like he was never away from the game. Full and wide, Dhoni reaches out and smashes it through extra cover. Goes to the boundary like a rocket!

Nortje to Dhoni, SIX, one-handed six over midwicket! Low full toss from Nortje, Dhoni swings hard, the bottom hand comes off but it doesn't matter when you hit it off the middle. It sails into the crowd who are going mad
Nortje to Dhoni, no run, full and wide outside off, Dhoni can't get under it and drives to long-off
Nortje to Dhoni, FOUR, four more for Dhonl! Full toss at the stumps, mid-on is in the ring and he comfortably hits it over the infield
Nortje to Dhoni, no run, yorker outside off, Dhoni squeezes it to point

Nortje to Dhoni, SIX, oh my goodness! Another terrific hit from Dhoni as he sends the last ball for a six. Old habits die hard. Low full toss outside off, he gets under it and carves it over extra cover. Nevertheless, it's the Capitals who come out on top and open their account this season

23:25 Local Time, 17:55 GMT, 23:25 IST: Phew that was some hitting from Dhoni towards the end to send the crowd into a frenzy. The game was long gone though. Barring the last couple of overs where Dhoni smacked it around, the Capitals were brilliant with the execution of their plans. The target of 192 looked achievable at the halfway stage on a good pitch and short boundaries. However, it didn't take long for Khaleel Ahmed to turn that narrative around with a brilliant opening spell that got rid of both the in-form openers. It wasn't just the dismissals, but the hold he had on someone like Rachin that really said a lot about how well he bowled. Rachin, who has been on fire so far in this tournament, couldn't get bat to ball for more than half of the 12 deliveries he faced, eventually getting caught for 2.

CSK did get going with a partnership between Ajinkya Rahane and Daryl Mitchell, but they were never allowed to break free. Axar Patel played a key role in those middle overs as he slipped in 3 miserly overs before Dube came to the middle. And when he did, the Capitals switched to the plan of bowling wide yorkers and cutters, assigning that role to the experience of Ishant, Nortje and Mukesh. They did the job asked of them, and the result was that Dube laboured to 18 off 17 balls with the rate going out of control. It was a night where Capitals executed a lot of their plans brilliantly to register their first win of the season over a dangerous team with so much batting depth.
Most runs by a designated WK in T20 cricket 8578 - Quinton de Kock 7721 - Jos Buttler 7036 - MS Dhoni* 6962 - Mohammad Rizwan 6454 - Kamran Akmal
Axar Patel's bowling this IPL 0/25(4) vs PBKS (ER: 6.25) 1/21(4) vs RR (ER: 5.25) 1/20(3) vs CSK (ER: 6.67)
Time for the presentations..

Nortje: (On his fitness) Felt a lot better, getting into things again. More game time, the better it will be. The training has been good, I focus on one or two areas on where I want to land it. I like to go straight yorker, but have been training on that wide yorker. (On bowling unit) We are building up slowly. The way the boys are starting- Khaleel, Mukesh and Ishant, to see the swing and speed is really exciting. Very encouraging for me as the 3rd or 4th change bowler in this line-up.

Ruturaj | CSK captain: I think I was pretty much happy with the way they (bowlers) came back after the start (powerplay). Restricting them to 191 was a good effort. The pitch was on the better side in the first innings. Second innings there was extra seam movement and spongy bounce. I felt he (Rachin) was missing it by a big margin. We couldn't get going in the first three overs and that was the difference. At the halfway stage it was getable. There was extra seam movement and we couldn't capitalize and we were always behind. We didn't get the big over to reduce the run rate. Not really (if an extra bowler in the line up with help in powerplay). Deepak is always used to bowling 3 overs. Even though the first four overs were good, the last two overs were expensive. After two good games you can expect the third game to go below par and that's nothing to worry about. Just two or three hits here and there, in the field if we had stopped one or two boundaries it could have been different.

Pant, DC captain: Bowlers have been clinical today. We've learnt from our mistake. He's been working hard from last two weeks (Shaw). We thought it's time to give him a chance and he flourished. It will depend on match to match, but if Mukesh can bowl at the death it'll be great. As a cricketer I've to give my 100 percent. Took some time initially as I haven't played much cricket in the last 1.5 years. This is something I've depended my life on. Always had the self-belief that whatever happens, it's important to come back to the ground.

Khaleel, POTM: Have worked hard in the domestic season. Played a lot of matches in the last six months which has helped me know my game better. Love it when the ball swings and the batters get beaten. Have tried to figure out how I can keep myself fit. Red-ball game teaches you a lot about how the ball is coming out of the hand. Ultimate goal is to play for India.
